When you drop this into Cursor, it will follow this 7-day sprint to a live site.

Day 1: Project Initialization & Global Branding
Action: Create a Next.js 14 project. Set up Tailwind with a custom color palette: kingdom-gold, royal-black, and pure-white.

Output: A clean, empty project with a global layout and SEO metadata for "Kingdom Commerce."

Day 2: The Navigation & Footer (The Gates of the Kingdom)
Action: Build a sticky navigation bar with a search icon, "Start Selling" button, and category dropdown. Build a "Global Impact" footer.

Output: Fully responsive navigation that works on iPhone and Desktop.

Day 3: Hero Section & High-Impact Value Prop
Action: Create a hero section with a high-resolution placeholder for Black-owned brand imagery and a clear CTA: "Support the Culture. Build the Kingdom."

Output: A visually stunning entry point.

Day 4: Multi-Vendor Product Grid (The Marketplace)
Action: Create a mock product grid component. Include badges for "Youth Owned," "Global Shipping," and "Verified Vendor."

Output: A 4-column grid (2 on mobile) showing what the marketplace will look like.

Day 5: Vendor Storefront Template (Static)
Action: Build a profile page for a hypothetical vendor. Include a banner, bio, and their specific product catalog.

Output: A template that allows any seller to see how their "Kingdom" will look.

Day 6: Cart & Checkout UI (Static)
Action: Build the slide-over cart and a 3-step checkout page (Shipping, Kingdom Pay Preview, Review).

Output: The full user journey from discovery to "purchase."

Day 7: Netlify Launch
Action: Guide the user through git init, creating a GitHub repo, and connecting it to Netlify.

Output: A live URL (e.g., kingdom-commerce.netlify.app) to show investors and vendors.

